User Stories:

1. Unified Interactable Academic Calendar

User Story (Before – The Problem)
Jordan is a student taking several classes while also participating in campus activities. Each class has its own syllabus, assignment list, and exam schedule posted in different places online. Jordan constantly switches between multiple platforms and documents to figure out what is due and when. Sometimes deadlines overlap without Jordan realizing it until the last minute, causing unnecessary stress and rushed work.

User Story (After – The Solution)
Jordan opens the Unified Interactable Academic Calendar, which shows all classes, assignments, exams, and events in one place. The calendar provides a clear visual overview of the week and month, allowing Jordan to easily see upcoming commitments. If a deadline changes or Jordan needs to adjust a personal task, it can be edited directly in the calendar. With everything visible in one interface, Jordan can plan ahead and manage time much more effectively.

2. Assignment and Exam Tracking

User Story (Before – The Problem)
Maria often struggles to remember every assignment and exam date across her courses. Some deadlines are listed on course pages while others are mentioned in lectures or emails. Because of this, Maria sometimes forgets about smaller assignments until the day they are due, leaving little time to complete them properly.

User Story (After – The Solution)
Maria uses the Assignment and Exam Tracking feature to enter and manage all her academic deadlines in one place. The system sends reminders as deadlines approach, helping her stay aware of upcoming work. Instead of constantly checking multiple sources, Maria relies on the tracker to keep everything organized and visible. This helps her stay prepared and reduces the risk of missing important deadlines.

3. Event Manager

User Story (Before – The Problem)
Kevin is active in several clubs and organizations on campus while also maintaining a full academic schedule. Club meetings and events are announced through group chats and emails, which Kevin has to manually keep track of. Occasionally, a meeting conflicts with an assignment deadline or study time, but Kevin does not realize the conflict until it is too late.

User Story (After – The Solution)
Kevin uses the Event Manager to track club meetings, social events, and extracurricular activities separately from his academic tasks. The system shows how these events align with his academic commitments, making it easy to spot scheduling conflicts. By viewing everything together, Kevin can balance his academic responsibilities and social activities more effectively.

4. Task Prioritization

User Story (Before – The Problem)
Samantha often feels overwhelmed when several assignments are due in the same week. She spends time trying to decide which tasks are most important based on how much they affect her grade and how challenging the class is. Without a clear way to prioritize, Samantha sometimes spends too much time on smaller assignments while neglecting more important ones.

User Story (After – The Solution)
Samantha uses the Task Prioritization feature, which automatically sorts her assignments based on how much they contribute to the final grade and how important the class is to her. The system highlights high-impact tasks so she can focus her effort where it matters most. With priorities clearly organized, Samantha can study more efficiently and feel less overwhelmed by her workload.
